al matching using other\nwhite dwarfs with non-Gaia data indicate a radial velocity in the interval\n(-60, -70) km/s.\n  Conclusions. These results confirm the future flyby of WD 0810-353 near the\nSolar System, although the relative velocity could be high enough or the\nminimum approach distance large enough to preclude any significant perturbation\non the Oort cloud.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2022 17:24:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-30"}
