 of our astrophysical\nbackground parameter space, and its significance can vary appreciably. Further\nscrutiny is necessary to improve the understanding of these lower energy cosmic\nrays. Finally, we note that even if an excess signal is found in these\nenergies, the current background uncertainties do not allow us to accurately\ndeduce its underlying particle properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2022 18:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
