on of the\ncorresponding irreducible components. The converse of this statement is also\ntrue when the Serre weights are chosen to be sufficiently generic. Furthermore,\nwe show that the number of top-dimensional components in a codimension one\nintersection is related to the nature of the extension group of corresponding\nSerre weights.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2022 20:14:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 2 May 2023 14:03:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-03"}
